1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,978 --> 00:01:36,137
(A few days ago, FamilyMart)
I've done the math.

3
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:37,378
This round of layoffs,

4
00:01:37,777 --> 00:01:39,297
someone in our core teams

5
00:01:40,618 --> 00:01:41,777
will have to go.

6
00:01:42,378 --> 00:01:43,738
At least one person per group.

7
00:01:45,577 --> 00:01:47,978
I plan to cut the least attractive ones.

8
00:01:49,258 --> 00:01:51,057
That doesn't seem to be fair.

9
00:01:51,738 --> 00:01:52,978
They do the same work.

10
00:01:53,258 --> 00:01:54,777
If you're ugly and incompetent,

11
00:01:54,777 --> 00:01:55,697
you have to go.

12
00:01:56,417 --> 00:01:57,738
So we can hire someone prettier.

13
00:01:59,018 --> 00:02:00,057
You could do the same.

14
00:02:00,618 --> 00:02:02,857
My group only has a few underperformers.

15
00:02:03,258 --> 00:02:04,497
There are no unattractive ones.

16
00:02:05,018 --> 00:02:05,937
Your group?

17
00:02:06,297 --> 00:02:08,577
You're planning to fire Tao?

18
00:02:11,818 --> 00:02:13,818
Out with it. Who is Tao to you?

19
00:02:14,297 --> 00:02:16,058
You kept this well hidden.

20
00:02:17,457 --> 00:02:19,378
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

21
00:02:20,338 --> 00:02:22,658
She's my mentor's child.
I had no choice.

22
00:02:23,058 --> 00:02:23,897
Do you know

23
00:02:23,897 --> 00:02:25,697
her performance is dead last
in the group?

24
00:02:25,697 --> 00:02:26,417
I know, I know.

25
00:02:26,577 --> 00:02:27,737
Well, I just found out.

26
00:02:28,177 --> 00:02:29,258
I had to ask her myself.

27
00:02:30,857 --> 00:02:32,897
She's usually quite sensible.

28
00:02:33,457 --> 00:02:35,137
Never asked me for anything.

29
00:02:35,818 --> 00:02:37,577
Now that she knows
she's getting laid off,

30
00:02:38,098 --> 00:02:40,017
she's been losing sleep
night after night.

31
00:02:41,697 --> 00:02:43,338
Alright, I got it.

32
00:02:44,778 --> 00:02:45,457
Thanks.

33
00:02:47,874 --> 00:02:48,610
(Compassion)

34
00:02:50,082 --> 00:02:50,824
(Shanshui Hall)

35
00:02:50,824 --> 00:02:51,784
(Blessing in disguise)

36
00:02:52,706 --> 00:02:53,480
(Rebound)

37
00:02:54,626 --> 00:02:58,760
=Episode 6=
(Opportunity)

38
00:03:05,297 --> 00:03:06,737
I know this wasn't right of me.

39
00:03:07,137 --> 00:03:09,218
But we had no choice.

40
00:03:09,218 --> 00:03:10,378
Say whatever you want.

41
00:03:11,297 --> 00:03:12,297
I know you won't listen.

42
00:03:12,297 --> 00:03:13,098
I had to go to Fan.

43
00:03:13,098 --> 00:03:14,378
This is a multi-million project.

44
00:03:14,378 --> 00:03:15,137
You... you...

45
00:03:16,017 --> 00:03:16,737
You know...

46
00:03:16,857 --> 00:03:17,938
I'm free tomorrow.

47
00:03:19,938 --> 00:03:20,938
Tomorrow it is then?

48
00:03:29,297 --> 00:03:30,378
Hello, Fengyun Express.

49
00:03:30,378 --> 00:03:31,297
You're Qiaoqiao, right?

50
00:03:31,658 --> 00:03:32,778
You have a COD package.

51
00:03:32,778 --> 00:03:35,017
When will you be home today?
I'll deliver it.

52
00:03:35,137 --> 00:03:36,218
Perhaps around

53
00:03:37,017 --> 00:03:38,098
11 PM or so.

54
00:03:38,098 --> 00:03:39,658
Eleven? That's too late.

55
00:03:39,818 --> 00:03:41,938
What time do you leave tomorrow morning?

56
00:03:42,577 --> 00:03:45,258
I leave around 7 AM.

57
00:03:45,538 --> 00:03:46,938
You work such long hours.

58
00:03:48,218 --> 00:03:49,058
How about this?

59
00:03:49,737 --> 00:03:51,338
When you're almost home these days,

60
00:03:51,498 --> 00:03:52,457
give me a call.

61
00:03:52,818 --> 00:03:54,818
If I'm nearby, I'll drop it off. Okay?

62
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:55,778
You have my number?

63
00:03:57,897 --> 00:03:58,737
Write it down.

64
00:03:58,857 --> 00:03:59,457
Okay.

65
00:04:01,538 --> 00:04:02,778
Alright, thanks.

66
00:04:10,306 --> 00:04:12,386
(Fan)

67
00:04:20,497 --> 00:04:22,338
Ms. Tan, anything else to add?

68
00:04:23,658 --> 00:04:24,497
This is fine for now.

69
00:04:31,497 --> 00:04:35,338
I bet right now you're scheming
how to convince me to hire you

70
00:04:35,458 --> 00:04:37,937
while cursing me nonstop.

71
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:39,817
You're half right.

72
00:04:40,497 --> 00:04:41,297
The first half.

73
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:44,898
Did your boss give you trouble?

74
00:04:48,497 --> 00:04:49,538
That day,

75
00:04:50,297 --> 00:04:51,778
I shouldn't have lost my temper.

76
00:04:52,497 --> 00:04:54,458
You're my client, after all.

77
00:04:54,778 --> 00:04:56,218
I shouldn't have spoken like that.

78
00:04:56,778 --> 00:04:57,617
I'm sorry.

79
00:04:58,177 --> 00:04:59,817
So he really gave you trouble.

80
00:05:01,098 --> 00:05:03,778
My boss called me in
because I caused him trouble.

81
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:12,497
Okay, truthfully,

82
00:05:13,338 --> 00:05:14,617
I've been a bit on edge lately,

83
00:05:14,937 --> 00:05:16,617
because of other projects.

84
00:05:17,057 --> 00:05:17,658
Sorry.

85
00:05:21,937 --> 00:05:22,458
Okay.

86
00:05:23,018 --> 00:05:24,338
Apology accepted.

87
00:05:25,297 --> 00:05:26,177
Thank you.

88
00:05:27,658 --> 00:05:28,497
I know

89
00:05:28,658 --> 00:05:32,057
you lost the GST project
because of your wife's speech.

90
00:05:33,497 --> 00:05:34,617
Did Xiao Yang tell you?

91
00:05:35,018 --> 00:05:37,098
He also has a duty
to brief me about you.

92
00:05:38,218 --> 00:05:41,617
Besides, I'm a major client of GST.

93
00:05:42,098 --> 00:05:45,218
Seems I have no secrets left with you.

94
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:47,538
I watched your wife's speech.

95
00:05:47,857 --> 00:05:49,057
I quite like her.

96
00:05:50,417 --> 00:05:53,737
Actually, not just sales ladies
face these issues.

97
00:05:54,297 --> 00:05:55,098
Take me,

98
00:05:55,617 --> 00:05:57,338
even as a boss,

99
00:05:57,538 --> 00:05:59,698
I'm often looked down on,

100
00:06:00,177 --> 00:06:01,857
slandered and harassed.

101
00:06:03,737 --> 00:06:06,177
But I don't dare to speak out
like your wife does.

102
00:06:07,218 --> 00:06:08,658
I can only keep it bottled up.

103
00:06:09,658 --> 00:06:11,857
These were all pre-arranged.

104
00:06:13,177 --> 00:06:14,338
Pre-arranged?

105
00:06:15,057 --> 00:06:15,617
That's right.

106
00:06:17,098 --> 00:06:19,737
GST holds a sales promoter conference
every quarter.

107
00:06:19,737 --> 00:06:21,098
Had you heard about it before?

108
00:06:21,857 --> 00:06:23,177
So it was intentional?

109
00:06:24,297 --> 00:06:26,617
My wife is in a difficult position
at the company now.

110
00:06:27,098 --> 00:06:29,297
The one who got into trouble
was her direct superior.

111
00:06:29,338 --> 00:06:31,538
The one being harassed
was her female subordinate.

112
00:06:31,857 --> 00:06:35,057
For her, offense is the best defense.

113
00:06:35,857 --> 00:06:38,297
Besides, GST urgently needs
crisis PR right now.

114
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:40,297
What better way to win

115
00:06:40,658 --> 00:06:42,617
public sympathy
than showing vulnerability?

116
00:06:44,098 --> 00:06:45,538
You taught her that?

117
00:06:47,177 --> 00:06:48,538
I said negotiate through pressure,

118
00:06:48,538 --> 00:06:50,538
not to attack wildly like this!

119
00:06:50,538 --> 00:06:52,698
You felt cornered at the company,

120
00:06:53,098 --> 00:06:55,417
so you decided to burn everything down.

121
00:06:55,417 --> 00:06:56,817
That's not it.

122
00:06:58,817 --> 00:07:00,218
Execution matters more.

123
00:07:00,698 --> 00:07:02,617
But she succeeded,
and you lost the project.

124
00:07:04,377 --> 00:07:05,617
This sounds unprofessional,

125
00:07:06,377 --> 00:07:07,377
but in my heart,

126
00:07:08,138 --> 00:07:09,576
she matters more than any project.

127
00:07:09,778 --> 00:07:11,937
Didn't I tell you I was pitching
to your company?

128
00:07:12,698 --> 00:07:14,057
We were about to close the deal,

129
00:07:14,057 --> 00:07:15,737
but now, how do I face them?

130
00:07:16,138 --> 00:07:18,257
Actually, even if she loses her job,

131
00:07:18,377 --> 00:07:20,138
we can still live very well.

132
00:07:20,257 --> 00:07:21,257
I can support her.

133
00:07:22,018 --> 00:07:23,018
But I know

134
00:07:23,578 --> 00:07:24,808
she loves her job,

135
00:07:25,318 --> 00:07:27,578
just like I love mine,

136
00:07:27,698 --> 00:07:29,257
and you love yours.

137
00:07:31,817 --> 00:07:32,317
Ms. Tan.

138
00:07:33,057 --> 00:07:34,257
No need to call me that.

139
00:07:34,578 --> 00:07:36,218
Call me Stella from now on.

140
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,257
Stella.

141
00:07:40,018 --> 00:07:41,138
Didn't Xiao Yang tell you?

142
00:07:41,698 --> 00:07:44,377
I've already gotten
the GST project back.

143
00:07:48,138 --> 00:07:48,937
Congratulations.

144
00:07:49,898 --> 00:07:50,698
Thanks.

145
00:07:52,737 --> 00:07:55,377
Dad, everything's fine.

146
00:07:56,057 --> 00:07:57,177
Don't worry.

147
00:07:58,817 --> 00:08:00,377
Busy? Of course.

148
00:08:00,857 --> 00:08:01,937
But being busy is good.

149
00:08:02,417 --> 00:08:04,297
The real worry
is having nothing to do, right?

150
00:08:08,497 --> 00:08:09,978
The leaders treat me well.

151
00:08:10,257 --> 00:08:11,978
They've included me in several projects.

152
00:08:12,737 --> 00:08:13,617
Gennadiy.

153
00:08:14,937 --> 00:08:16,377
You even tried that wine.

154
00:08:16,377 --> 00:08:18,057
You said it was tasty, remember?

155
00:08:19,857 --> 00:08:20,698
Yeah.

156
00:08:20,857 --> 00:08:22,578
That brand is our client.

157
00:08:25,737 --> 00:08:26,617
Don't worry.

158
00:08:26,937 --> 00:08:28,377
I'll take good care of myself.

159
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,298
The cost of living is high,

160
00:08:33,377 --> 00:08:34,857
but your daughter earns enough.

161
00:08:34,857 --> 00:08:35,617
Right?

162
00:08:36,617 --> 00:08:37,578
Got it.

163
00:08:38,938 --> 00:08:40,178
Don't worry.

164
00:08:42,218 --> 00:08:43,537
Alright.

165
00:08:43,537 --> 00:08:44,657
Take care of yourself too.

166
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,098
Gotta go now.

167
00:08:46,298 --> 00:08:47,497
I have a meeting soon.

168
00:08:48,698 --> 00:08:49,657
Hanging up now, bye.

169
00:09:11,497 --> 00:09:12,497
Why are you back so soon?

170
00:09:13,137 --> 00:09:13,698
About my...

171
00:09:14,938 --> 00:09:15,938
It's set.

172
00:09:16,178 --> 00:09:18,017
Meeting at their HQ tomorrow morning.

173
00:09:20,137 --> 00:09:20,938
Thank you so much.

174
00:09:21,698 --> 00:09:24,137
I knew you are the best
smooth talker with women.

175
00:09:24,617 --> 00:09:25,818
If I had half your skills,

176
00:09:25,818 --> 00:09:27,098
I'd be flying high by now!

177
00:09:28,017 --> 00:09:29,338
Why are you drinking alone here?

178
00:09:29,578 --> 00:09:31,458
Let's go out, my treat.

179
00:09:31,777 --> 00:09:33,338
I found a great spot recently.

180
00:09:33,497 --> 00:09:34,377
No, I'm tired.

181
00:09:35,737 --> 00:09:37,698
Li Dongming, this isn't like you.

182
00:09:37,938 --> 00:09:39,338
How can you say you're tired?

183
00:09:41,257 --> 00:09:41,818
I mean it.

184
00:09:41,818 --> 00:09:42,318
Another day.

185
00:09:42,857 --> 00:09:43,357
Another day.

186
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,617
Alright then, my treat another day.

187
00:09:49,298 --> 00:09:50,938
The employee evaluation scores are out.

188
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:54,137
I saw you raised Tao's score.

189
00:09:55,897 --> 00:09:56,397
Thank you.

190
00:10:10,082 --> 00:10:12,227
(27 Tao Ling, Li Dongming Team
28 Qiao Hailun, Li Dongming Team)

191
00:10:20,857 --> 00:10:23,017
I heard the comprehensive
evaluation scores are out.

192
00:10:24,017 --> 00:10:25,777
But they say it's confidential.

193
00:10:27,537 --> 00:10:29,897
Confidential for subordinates,
but not for superiors.

194
00:10:31,497 --> 00:10:33,137
I heard the evaluation scores

195
00:10:33,178 --> 00:10:35,017
will be the main basis for layoffs.

196
00:10:35,857 --> 00:10:36,857
You believe that?

197
00:10:37,418 --> 00:10:38,178
Why wouldn't I?

198
00:10:38,777 --> 00:10:39,897
Since ancient times,

199
00:10:40,017 --> 00:10:42,178
the sole criterion for layoffs

200
00:10:42,257 --> 00:10:43,857
has been one and only one.

201
00:10:45,178 --> 00:10:46,178
The boss's preferences.

202
00:10:51,497 --> 00:10:54,178
So the question is,
what are the boss's preferences?

203
00:10:54,298 --> 00:10:55,257
Who knows?

204
00:10:56,257 --> 00:10:58,497
If I knew, I wouldn't be working here.

205
00:11:00,617 --> 00:11:02,737
Qiao Hailun,
you've got the least to worry about.

206
00:11:02,737 --> 00:11:04,298
Mr. Li likes you so much.

207
00:11:04,537 --> 00:11:06,178
That's not true. Don't talk nonsense.

208
00:11:08,017 --> 00:11:09,497
Is there a possibility

209
00:11:10,698 --> 00:11:12,458
that the boss doesn't know
what to do either?

210
00:11:12,897 --> 00:11:13,777
Think about it.

211
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:16,137
We all graduated
from a top-tier university.

212
00:11:16,897 --> 00:11:18,938
We're working overtime
until 2 or 3 AM every day.

213
00:11:19,418 --> 00:11:20,137
Every one of us

214
00:11:20,978 --> 00:11:23,137
has both the qualifications
and the work ethic.

215
00:11:23,617 --> 00:11:25,458
If they really have to lay off someone,

216
00:11:26,017 --> 00:11:28,617
the boss can only
rely on personal preferences.

217
00:11:29,737 --> 00:11:31,058
You're quite understanding.

218
00:11:33,737 --> 00:11:34,777
Empathizing with the boss

219
00:11:35,418 --> 00:11:37,338
is my greatest joy in life.

220
00:11:44,897 --> 00:11:45,777
Tell me,

221
00:11:46,178 --> 00:11:48,178
among the bosses in our company,

222
00:11:48,897 --> 00:11:49,777
who's the lecher?

223
00:11:59,298 --> 00:12:00,017
You prudes.

224
00:12:07,497 --> 00:12:08,298
(Mr. Li)
(Come to my office.)

225
00:12:30,897 --> 00:12:31,857
Mr. Li, evening.

226
00:12:32,938 --> 00:12:33,497
Come in.

227
00:12:40,257 --> 00:12:40,777
Get the door.

228
00:12:53,017 --> 00:12:53,517
Take a seat.

229
00:12:55,257 --> 00:12:55,857
Mr. Li,

230
00:12:57,617 --> 00:12:58,857
is the company letting me go?

231
00:13:04,418 --> 00:13:05,137
I knew it.

232
00:13:32,298 --> 00:13:33,017
Don't worry.

233
00:13:33,017 --> 00:13:34,017
The evaluation results

234
00:13:34,777 --> 00:13:35,657
are confidential.

235
00:13:36,058 --> 00:13:37,178
Scores won't be leaked.

236
00:13:37,178 --> 00:13:39,058
Externally, we'll say

237
00:13:39,857 --> 00:13:40,818
you resigned.

238
00:13:41,617 --> 00:13:43,137
It won't affect your future job.

239
00:13:44,497 --> 00:13:46,617
I'm afraid I'll never find another job.

240
00:13:50,377 --> 00:13:52,298
Here. I'll write you
a recommendation letter.

241
00:13:53,298 --> 00:13:56,257
That might help with your job hunt.

242
00:13:56,777 --> 00:13:58,777
If any new company
wants a background check,

243
00:13:58,777 --> 00:14:00,178
just give them my number.

244
00:14:00,537 --> 00:14:01,537
I'll vouch for you.

245
00:14:06,377 --> 00:14:07,178
Thank you, Mr. Li.

246
00:14:11,857 --> 00:14:12,578
All the best.

247
00:14:30,178 --> 00:14:30,698
Oh, right.

248
00:14:35,418 --> 00:14:36,017
(Kangya Group Project Research)
What's this?

249
00:14:38,537 --> 00:14:40,257
The preliminary research
on Kangya Group?

250
00:14:41,017 --> 00:14:41,737
Did I ask for it?

251
00:14:42,657 --> 00:14:43,818
I prepared it in advance.

252
00:14:44,617 --> 00:14:45,938
I was afraid that when you ask,

253
00:14:46,857 --> 00:14:47,897
I won't have enough time.

254
00:14:49,137 --> 00:14:51,137
Why do you think
I can land this project?

255
00:14:51,617 --> 00:14:54,137
You were there when negotiations
with Tan Min broke down.

256
00:14:55,058 --> 00:14:55,857
I believe

257
00:14:57,098 --> 00:14:58,137
as long as you want it,

258
00:14:58,938 --> 00:15:00,777
you can definitely win this project.

259
00:15:01,098 --> 00:15:03,377
And as long as Ms. Tan isn't blind,

260
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:06,178
she can see that you're the best.

261
00:15:10,938 --> 00:15:12,657
We've secured the Kangya project.

262
00:15:15,257 --> 00:15:16,058
Really?

263
00:15:16,137 --> 00:15:17,938
We'll discuss the details next week.

264
00:15:22,418 --> 00:15:23,257
That's fantastic!

265
00:15:32,537 --> 00:15:33,537
It's just a shame

266
00:15:36,017 --> 00:15:37,418
I won't be part of it

267
00:15:41,178 --> 00:15:42,497
or work with you anymore.

268
00:15:58,857 --> 00:16:00,617
Perhaps you can still
stay on the project.

269
00:16:05,857 --> 00:16:06,938
Deciding

270
00:16:07,338 --> 00:16:09,017
an employee's fate

271
00:16:09,017 --> 00:16:10,897
based solely on one evaluation score

272
00:16:10,897 --> 00:16:12,657
is too arbitrary and unscientific.

273
00:16:13,257 --> 00:16:15,637
Especially for a consulting firm

274
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:19,137
that prides itself on talent strategy.

275
00:16:19,218 --> 00:16:20,338
We shouldn't do it that way.

276
00:16:24,777 --> 00:16:25,777
Are you saying

277
00:16:26,897 --> 00:16:27,938
you won't lay me off?

278
00:16:30,137 --> 00:16:31,737
Work hard from now on.

279
00:16:34,017 --> 00:16:34,897
Thank you, Mr. Li!

280
00:16:34,978 --> 00:16:36,418
(She hugged me so tightly.)

281
00:16:37,098 --> 00:16:39,897
(I knew her gratitude was genuine.)

282
00:16:39,897 --> 00:16:40,897
Thank you, Mr. Li.

283
00:16:40,897 --> 00:16:41,777
(But she didn't know)

284
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:44,818
(that I was grateful to her too.)

285
00:16:45,497 --> 00:16:48,137
(Everyone around me,
including Zhao Mei,)

286
00:16:48,578 --> 00:16:49,978
(has so many ulterior motives.)

287
00:16:50,578 --> 00:16:52,058
(But she's different.)

288
00:16:52,537 --> 00:16:53,978
(She showed me how real she was.)

289
00:17:19,418 --> 00:17:20,057
Liang.

290
00:17:20,938 --> 00:17:22,057
- Congratulations.
- Mr. Ke.

291
00:17:22,138 --> 00:17:23,898
- Mr. Ke.
- Your business keeps growing.

292
00:17:24,138 --> 00:17:24,658
Thank you.

293
00:17:24,658 --> 00:17:26,057
And you're looking more elegant.

294
00:17:27,297 --> 00:17:30,898
For today's crab feast, I've specially
prepared three wines for everyone.

295
00:17:31,178 --> 00:17:33,378
What our sommelier is pouring now

296
00:17:33,378 --> 00:17:35,458
is Moonlight City Vintage Champagne.

297
00:17:35,817 --> 00:17:36,577
This champagne

298
00:17:36,577 --> 00:17:38,777
has been properly chilled
in an ice bucket.

299
00:17:39,257 --> 00:17:40,418
The second wine

300
00:17:40,418 --> 00:17:43,618
is Gennadiy 25-Year-Old.

301
00:17:44,138 --> 00:17:46,497
I brought a limited edition today.

302
00:17:48,277 --> 00:17:50,938
Finally, our Gold Label Gustav.

303
00:17:51,618 --> 00:17:52,858
How does that saying go?

304
00:17:53,418 --> 00:17:57,418
Cognac endures forever,
classics live on forever, right?

305
00:17:57,537 --> 00:17:58,777
Live on.

306
00:17:59,017 --> 00:18:00,777
The legend does live on.

307
00:18:01,898 --> 00:18:02,658
Ms. Liang,

308
00:18:03,178 --> 00:18:06,257
eating crab calls for yellow wine.

309
00:18:06,658 --> 00:18:08,257
So, do you have yellow wine?

310
00:18:08,618 --> 00:18:10,537
Yes! What don't I have?

311
00:18:10,898 --> 00:18:12,777
I specifically brought two jars

312
00:18:12,777 --> 00:18:14,537
of fifty-year-old Shaoxing yellow wine.

313
00:18:14,537 --> 00:18:15,898
Ask me if you need some.

314
00:18:16,158 --> 00:18:16,658
Fifty years.

315
00:18:16,658 --> 00:18:17,658
Especially for you.

316
00:18:17,658 --> 00:18:18,257
I need some.

317
00:18:18,257 --> 00:18:19,777
Your requests can't stump Liang.

318
00:18:20,898 --> 00:18:21,777
Ms. Liang.

319
00:18:22,057 --> 00:18:25,938
Is it not quite appropriate
to drink yellow wine at your banquet?

320
00:18:26,418 --> 00:18:29,097
Mr. Zhang, just hearing that tells me
you're not familiar with me.

321
00:18:29,737 --> 00:18:31,138
All my friends know

322
00:18:31,138 --> 00:18:34,297
I have only one principle for drinking,
to drink happily.

323
00:18:34,577 --> 00:18:35,898
As for what wine we drink,

324
00:18:35,898 --> 00:18:37,178
as long as it makes us happy,

325
00:18:37,178 --> 00:18:38,497
it doesn't matter, right?

326
00:18:38,497 --> 00:18:39,777
Right.

327
00:18:39,817 --> 00:18:41,698
Yes! As long as today,

328
00:18:41,858 --> 00:18:43,497
we don't drink Wilson's wine.

329
00:18:43,658 --> 00:18:46,097
Any wine is fine, Ms. Liang.

330
00:18:46,138 --> 00:18:48,097
Ke, you're teasing me again, aren't you?

331
00:18:48,097 --> 00:18:48,898
Let me tell you,

332
00:18:48,898 --> 00:18:50,898
I'll have several more drinks with you.

333
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:52,497
Drink until we're drunk!

334
00:18:52,497 --> 00:18:54,218
Let's see who outdrinks whom.

335
00:18:54,418 --> 00:18:56,418
Today, the chef has prepared for you

336
00:18:56,418 --> 00:18:58,378
hairy crabs brought over
from Yangcheng Lake.

337
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,017
Alright! Then let's begin.

338
00:19:00,938 --> 00:19:03,658
Let's raise our
Moonlight City Vintage Champagne.

339
00:19:04,017 --> 00:19:04,658
Cheers!

340
00:19:04,658 --> 00:19:05,418
Cheers!

341
00:19:05,418 --> 00:19:06,978
Cheers!

342
00:19:20,257 --> 00:19:21,218
Thank you, Mr. Li.

343
00:19:21,337 --> 00:19:23,418
Mr. Zhang, leaving so early today?

344
00:19:23,418 --> 00:19:25,097
I'm quite unhappy about that.

345
00:19:25,297 --> 00:19:27,378
I really have something to do today.

346
00:19:27,658 --> 00:19:28,938
Next time, if you invite me,

347
00:19:29,337 --> 00:19:31,138
I promise to stay with you
till the very end.

348
00:19:31,737 --> 00:19:32,237
Alright?

349
00:19:33,138 --> 00:19:34,097
To the very end.

350
00:19:34,178 --> 00:19:34,678
Okay.

351
00:19:34,737 --> 00:19:35,938
Come on, pinky swear!

352
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:37,458
Don't lie to me!

353
00:19:37,978 --> 00:19:39,297
Okay!

354
00:19:40,297 --> 00:19:42,658
That limited edition wine you mentioned?

355
00:19:42,737 --> 00:19:43,777
I need it for my girl.

356
00:19:44,378 --> 00:19:45,017
You got it, huh?

357
00:19:45,858 --> 00:19:46,497
Liang.

358
00:19:46,497 --> 00:19:48,458
Of course, how could I not?

359
00:19:48,458 --> 00:19:49,178
You can't do this.

360
00:19:49,337 --> 00:19:49,938
Then I'm off.

361
00:19:50,138 --> 00:19:50,978
Okay.

362
00:19:52,337 --> 00:19:54,218
Alright, Mr. Zhang, take care.

363
00:19:54,817 --> 00:19:55,618
Bye-bye.

364
00:20:08,337 --> 00:20:09,057
Had some drinks?

365
00:20:11,658 --> 00:20:12,898
Why are you lying face down?

366
00:20:13,858 --> 00:20:14,698
My back hurts.

367
00:20:14,698 --> 00:20:16,057
I can only type this way.

368
00:20:17,418 --> 00:20:19,257
I'll probably have to sleep

369
00:20:19,577 --> 00:20:20,218
on the couch.

370
00:20:22,698 --> 00:20:23,737
What about you?

371
00:20:23,737 --> 00:20:24,577
What do you mean?

372
00:20:25,418 --> 00:20:27,297
Didn't Li Dongming
call you into his office

373
00:20:27,297 --> 00:20:28,698
and then you both left together?

374
00:20:29,618 --> 00:20:30,497
What did you do?

375
00:20:30,737 --> 00:20:31,458
Nothing.

376
00:20:33,737 --> 00:20:34,898
Are you serious?

377
00:20:35,938 --> 00:20:36,858
Of course.

378
00:20:38,817 --> 00:20:41,497
Then what's that hickey on your neck?

379
00:20:44,898 --> 00:20:45,898
What hickey?

380
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:53,297
Where?

381
00:20:53,658 --> 00:20:54,938
Just kidding.

382
00:20:57,978 --> 00:20:59,297
Are you crazy?

383
00:20:59,658 --> 00:21:01,418
Li Dongming called me to his office

384
00:21:01,577 --> 00:21:03,458
to talk about the GST project.

385
00:21:03,898 --> 00:21:07,178
Then he asked me to accompany him
to entertain clients. That's all.

386
00:21:08,138 --> 00:21:09,658
If that's all, that's all.

387
00:21:10,497 --> 00:21:11,777
Look how worked up you got.

388
00:21:27,938 --> 00:21:29,898
There's really nothing
between me and him.

389
00:21:30,138 --> 00:21:31,817
Don't make jokes like that anymore.

390
00:21:34,378 --> 00:21:35,658
But among us,

391
00:21:35,658 --> 00:21:37,418
he really does prefer taking you out.

392
00:21:39,817 --> 00:21:40,978
Maybe I'm more obedient.

393
00:21:42,297 --> 00:21:42,817
What?

394
00:21:43,497 --> 00:21:44,178
Obedient?

395
00:21:45,057 --> 00:21:47,178
That's quite far-fetched.

396
00:21:48,898 --> 00:21:50,618
Do you know what others say about you?

397
00:21:53,658 --> 00:21:56,698
They say the reason Li Dongming
likes taking you out so much

398
00:21:56,698 --> 00:21:58,898
is because you have big boobs.

399
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:00,277
What?

400
00:22:02,418 --> 00:22:03,698
That's utter nonsense!

401
00:22:03,698 --> 00:22:05,577
So I'm just giving you a heads-up, okay?

402
00:22:08,658 --> 00:22:10,097
I don't need that kind of heads-up.

403
00:22:11,057 --> 00:22:12,378
Anyway, believe it or not,

404
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:15,658
there's really nothing going on
between us. He's my boss.

405
00:22:15,898 --> 00:22:17,938
I can't decide who he takes
to business dinners.

406
00:22:17,938 --> 00:22:18,658
Besides,

407
00:22:18,698 --> 00:22:19,898
what people say about me

408
00:22:19,978 --> 00:22:21,297
isn't something I can control.

409
00:22:22,418 --> 00:22:24,938
So tell me the truth,
do you actually like him?

410
00:22:25,057 --> 00:22:26,497
What do you mean, like him?

411
00:22:26,577 --> 00:22:29,297
He's my boss, and I work for him.

412
00:22:29,418 --> 00:22:29,918
He and I...

413
00:22:31,577 --> 00:22:33,458
We have a professional relationship.

414
00:22:34,337 --> 00:22:34,898
Wait,

415
00:22:34,898 --> 00:22:37,337
why do you keep asking
such strange questions?

416
00:22:37,378 --> 00:22:38,097
You.

417
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:40,138
Didn't I say it already?

418
00:22:40,297 --> 00:22:42,658
I'm just warning you to be careful.

419
00:22:42,898 --> 00:22:44,978
These kinds of situations
can be messy to handle.

420
00:22:45,658 --> 00:22:46,938
I know that.

421
00:22:47,658 --> 00:22:48,698
I'm not stupid.

422
00:22:53,817 --> 00:22:55,378
Some people!

423
00:23:09,658 --> 00:23:12,337
I really meant well
when I told you all that earlier.

424
00:23:12,497 --> 00:23:14,178
If you don't like how I put it,

425
00:23:14,418 --> 00:23:15,497
just ignore it.

426
00:23:17,817 --> 00:23:20,178
Your birthday's coming up.
Happy birthday.

427
00:23:20,497 --> 00:23:21,218
This is for you.

428
00:23:29,458 --> 00:23:30,418
Thank you, Tao.

429
00:24:03,978 --> 00:24:05,032
(LAN Communications)
I was just about to ask

430
00:24:05,032 --> 00:24:06,057
when you're coming over.

431
00:24:06,618 --> 00:24:07,337
I'm almost there.

432
00:24:08,898 --> 00:24:09,577
Uh,

433
00:24:11,138 --> 00:24:11,898
I saw...

434
00:24:12,138 --> 00:24:12,938
Honey,

435
00:24:13,138 --> 00:24:14,658
take a look at the third-round draft.

436
00:24:14,658 --> 00:24:15,297
Okay.

437
00:24:17,418 --> 00:24:18,418
We'll wait for you.

438
00:24:19,138 --> 00:24:20,577
Alright, let's talk when I see you.

439
00:24:26,178 --> 00:24:27,057
(Does Li Dongming)

440
00:24:27,378 --> 00:24:30,898
provide enough physical value for you?

441
00:24:31,297 --> 00:24:32,378
He... Well,

442
00:24:33,097 --> 00:24:35,178
he usually enjoys working out.

443
00:24:35,297 --> 00:24:36,938
And people from consulting firms

444
00:24:36,938 --> 00:24:38,858
tend to have a lot of energy.

445
00:24:40,817 --> 00:24:44,378
Plus, we've only been married
for two years,

446
00:24:44,458 --> 00:24:46,138
so we're still newlyweds.

447
00:24:49,817 --> 00:24:51,378
(Thinking about how happy she looked,)

448
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:53,017
(I feel conflicted.)

449
00:24:53,658 --> 00:24:56,418
(What kind of best friend
truly counts as a good one?)

450
00:24:56,737 --> 00:24:57,537
(Do I share)

451
00:24:57,537 --> 00:24:58,978
(LAN Communications)
(everything I see,)

452
00:24:59,337 --> 00:25:00,658
(or do I selectively hide things)

453
00:25:00,978 --> 00:25:03,418
(to ensure she can stay happy longer?)

454
00:25:03,658 --> 00:25:05,218
The comments need to keep going.

455
00:25:05,418 --> 00:25:07,898
If the buzz drops suddenly again,
it'll seem fake.

456
00:25:07,938 --> 00:25:09,178
Your turn in one minute.

457
00:25:09,237 --> 00:25:09,737
Okay. Wait.

458
00:25:09,737 --> 00:25:12,178
We have to keep it steady here
and don't let it drop.

459
00:25:12,658 --> 00:25:14,138
Alright, thanks.

460
00:25:14,138 --> 00:25:14,858
Over here.

461
00:25:16,618 --> 00:25:18,658
By the way, what were you
going to tell me earlier?

462
00:25:20,057 --> 00:25:20,817
Nothing.

463
00:25:20,898 --> 00:25:23,218
I wanted a supplier's contact info.

464
00:25:23,577 --> 00:25:24,418
But then I found it.

465
00:25:24,978 --> 00:25:25,618
Okay.

466
00:25:26,658 --> 00:25:27,698
Here's to everyone.

467
00:25:27,698 --> 00:25:28,257
Congrats.

468
00:25:28,257 --> 00:25:28,898
Cheers!

469
00:25:31,218 --> 00:25:32,497
(Ms. Lan, Founder of LAN Communications)
Let me summarize first.

470
00:25:33,178 --> 00:25:34,737
As of 9 AM today,

471
00:25:34,817 --> 00:25:36,577
we've secured four trending topics.

472
00:25:37,057 --> 00:25:38,344
The buzz score hit ten thousand.

473
00:25:38,817 --> 00:25:41,097
That means nearly ten million people

474
00:25:41,097 --> 00:25:43,337
have noticed our heroine, Zhao Mei.

475
00:25:43,337 --> 00:25:45,017
(Watching Zhao Mei
clear another hurdle,)

476
00:25:45,618 --> 00:25:47,057
(I was genuinely happy for her.)

477
00:25:48,138 --> 00:25:49,898
(But this was expected.)

478
00:25:50,618 --> 00:25:51,858
(She's always so capable.)

479
00:25:53,097 --> 00:25:54,618
(Being best friends for ten years,)

480
00:25:55,057 --> 00:25:56,257
(sometimes when I look at her)

481
00:25:56,458 --> 00:25:58,218
(I feel like
she's another version of me,)

482
00:25:59,097 --> 00:26:00,178
(the ideal me,)

483
00:26:01,138 --> 00:26:03,658
(capable, decisive, and lucky.)

484
00:26:04,938 --> 00:26:05,817
(I'm Liang Danning.)

485
00:26:05,938 --> 00:26:08,698
(From an ordinary sales lady
to a top VIP salesperson,)

486
00:26:09,297 --> 00:26:10,537
(for ten years, day by day,)

487
00:26:10,658 --> 00:26:14,138
(I've been drinking and selling liquor,
drinking and selling liquor.)

488
00:26:15,057 --> 00:26:18,178
(In middle age, with kids below,
an elderly mom above,)

489
00:26:18,497 --> 00:26:20,257
(and a useless husband in between,)

490
00:26:21,057 --> 00:26:23,378
(sometimes I think
life is just pointless.)

491
00:26:24,257 --> 00:26:27,618
(How could someone as smart, kind,
and hardworking as me)

492
00:26:28,178 --> 00:26:29,817
(have it so hard?)

493
00:26:30,537 --> 00:26:32,698
(But still, I have to thank heaven)

494
00:26:33,297 --> 00:26:35,138
(for getting me
into imported liquor sales.)

495
00:26:35,497 --> 00:26:38,618
(At least, I can get drunk for free.)

496
00:26:39,337 --> 00:26:41,138
Yes, I was just about to bring it over.

497
00:26:41,138 --> 00:26:42,178
Someone's home, right?

498
00:26:43,418 --> 00:26:44,418
Okay.

499
00:26:45,698 --> 00:26:47,297
What? You want two more bottles?

500
00:26:47,737 --> 00:26:48,938
That might not be possible.

501
00:26:49,218 --> 00:26:51,458
This is Gennadiy Fifty-Year.

502
00:26:51,458 --> 00:26:53,218
There are only six bottles domestically

503
00:26:53,297 --> 00:26:54,658
and fifty bottles worldwide.

504
00:26:55,337 --> 00:26:56,097
Okay.

505
00:26:56,097 --> 00:26:57,178
Alright. See you soon.

506
00:26:59,297 --> 00:27:00,577
You scared me to death!

507
00:27:00,858 --> 00:27:03,458
These are the last two bottles
of 50-year Gennadiy in the country.

508
00:27:04,337 --> 00:27:05,898
Alright, I'll get back to work.

509
00:27:05,898 --> 00:27:06,577
Okay.

510
00:27:06,658 --> 00:27:07,418
Drive carefully.

511
00:27:07,418 --> 00:27:08,378
Will do.

512
00:27:08,458 --> 00:27:08,978
Bye.

513
00:27:08,978 --> 00:27:09,658
Bye.

514
00:27:26,282 --> 00:27:28,980
(Shanshui Hall)

515
00:27:34,498 --> 00:27:38,146
(Shanshui Hall)

516
00:27:39,138 --> 00:27:41,858
Mr. Jin, I'm at your doorstep now.

517
00:27:41,898 --> 00:27:42,978
But there's no one here.

518
00:27:43,297 --> 00:27:46,178
Should I just leave the wine
on the ground for you?

519
00:27:56,297 --> 00:27:57,057
What are you doing?

520
00:28:01,057 --> 00:28:02,257
You must be Mrs. Jin?

521
00:28:02,618 --> 00:28:04,458
Hello, I'm Liang from GST.

522
00:28:04,458 --> 00:28:06,218
I'm here to deliver
some wine to Mr. Jin.

523
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:08,497
Should I give this wine directly to you?

524
00:28:13,138 --> 00:28:13,658
Okay.

525
00:28:17,138 --> 00:28:19,057
Be careful when you pick it up later.

526
00:28:21,698 --> 00:28:22,858
Here's my business card.

527
00:28:23,418 --> 00:28:26,097
If you have any questions,
you can call me.

528
00:28:26,418 --> 00:28:28,817
On behalf of the company,
we thank Mr. Jin for his patronage.

529
00:28:30,178 --> 00:28:33,658
I think you're using the company's name
to represent yourself, aren't you?

530
00:28:34,737 --> 00:28:36,698
I've seen enough vixens like you.

531
00:28:37,138 --> 00:28:38,737
I'm hanging a peach wood sword here

532
00:28:38,938 --> 00:28:40,737
to ward off hussies like you.

533
00:28:43,658 --> 00:28:45,898
Mrs. Jin, you've misunderstood.
I'm not a vixen

534
00:28:45,898 --> 00:28:46,858
or a hussy.

535
00:28:46,858 --> 00:28:47,898
I'm here to deliver wine.

536
00:28:48,418 --> 00:28:50,057
If there's nothing else,
I'll be leaving.

537
00:28:53,458 --> 00:28:56,297
Mr. Jin, the wine is delivered.
Your wife received it.

538
00:28:57,658 --> 00:29:00,577
Talk about rotten luck!
Misfortune really came knocking.

539
00:29:05,337 --> 00:29:06,537
Sirius! No biting!

540
00:29:06,737 --> 00:29:07,257
Sirius!

541
00:29:07,577 --> 00:29:08,097
Sirius!

542
00:29:08,337 --> 00:29:09,458
Come here, Sirius!

543
00:29:09,737 --> 00:29:10,257
Sirius!

544
00:29:10,418 --> 00:29:10,918
Get back!

545
00:29:11,978 --> 00:29:12,478
Sirius!

546
00:29:13,858 --> 00:29:14,358
Sirius!

547
00:29:15,978 --> 00:29:16,478
Sirius!

548
00:29:19,418 --> 00:29:20,898
Don't let your dog just bite people!

549
00:29:21,257 --> 00:29:23,698
He's protecting his owner.
I can't hold him back.

550
00:29:24,297 --> 00:29:24,797
Let's go.

551
00:29:30,337 --> 00:29:30,938
Are you okay?

552
00:29:31,978 --> 00:29:32,898
Thank you, Mr. Shen.

553
00:29:34,378 --> 00:29:35,138
Do you know me?

554
00:29:36,497 --> 00:29:38,737
I'm Liang Danning,
a salesperson from GST.

555
00:29:39,057 --> 00:29:40,057
This is my card.

556
00:29:40,898 --> 00:29:41,398
Here you go.

557
00:29:42,938 --> 00:29:43,698
You're bleeding.

558
00:29:43,978 --> 00:29:44,658
Yeah.

559
00:29:46,817 --> 00:29:47,497
Who you calling?

560
00:29:48,337 --> 00:29:49,297
911.

561
00:29:49,898 --> 00:29:51,178
I'll just leave my car here.

562
00:29:51,178 --> 00:29:53,577
If the security asks,
could you please explain for me?

563
00:29:53,817 --> 00:29:54,658
You're quite tough.

564
00:29:55,337 --> 00:29:57,577
No need for 911.
I was just about to head out.

565
00:29:58,178 --> 00:29:59,257
I'll give you a ride.

566
00:30:00,938 --> 00:30:02,178
Alright then. Thank you.

567
00:30:07,817 --> 00:30:08,777
Is it still bleeding?

568
00:30:11,418 --> 00:30:11,978
No.

569
00:30:14,777 --> 00:30:16,418
I feel like I've seen you before.

570
00:30:17,418 --> 00:30:17,978
Really?

571
00:30:19,497 --> 00:30:21,418
Last year's Distributor Conference?

572
00:30:23,017 --> 00:30:23,517
No.

573
00:30:25,218 --> 00:30:27,017
Then maybe the night Cocoon opened?

574
00:30:27,017 --> 00:30:28,057
I was there that night.

575
00:30:31,577 --> 00:30:33,057
Sorry, handsome. My apologies.

576
00:30:35,138 --> 00:30:37,138
That's right! That was the night.

577
00:30:37,817 --> 00:30:38,817
Right outside Cocoon.

578
00:30:40,097 --> 00:30:41,378
You even called me "Handsome".

579
00:30:44,418 --> 00:30:45,658
Well, I wasn't wrong, was I?

580
00:30:45,658 --> 00:30:47,378
You are handsome, after all.

581
00:30:48,257 --> 00:30:48,858
I'm flattered.

582
00:30:51,138 --> 00:30:52,577
Excuse me, I need to take this call.

583
00:30:52,577 --> 00:30:54,626
(Dong Yue)

584
00:30:56,458 --> 00:30:56,958
Yes.

585
00:30:59,378 --> 00:31:00,938
Okay, okay. No problem.

586
00:31:02,097 --> 00:31:03,458
I'll be your guarantor for this.

587
00:31:05,218 --> 00:31:05,718
By the way,

588
00:31:06,337 --> 00:31:07,658
come by the house on Saturday.

589
00:31:08,178 --> 00:31:10,337
(The boss actually gets
to go to Mr. Shen's house?)

590
00:31:11,057 --> 00:31:11,557
Okay.

591
00:31:11,978 --> 00:31:12,478
Bye.

592
00:31:21,698 --> 00:31:22,297
Danning.

593
00:31:24,577 --> 00:31:25,577
What are you doing here?

594
00:31:26,378 --> 00:31:27,418
What happened?

595
00:31:27,497 --> 00:31:29,138
Got bitten by a dog out of nowhere?

596
00:31:29,418 --> 00:31:30,737
Don't ask. A run of bad luck.

597
00:31:31,817 --> 00:31:33,057
Let me see the wound.

598
00:31:33,057 --> 00:31:34,057
Don't look.

599
00:31:34,138 --> 00:31:34,817
Does it hurt?

600
00:31:34,938 --> 00:31:35,737
No.

601
00:31:35,737 --> 00:31:36,698
Just got a few stitches.

602
00:31:36,858 --> 00:31:38,418
It's disgusting. I hate it myself.

603
00:31:39,057 --> 00:31:40,297
But I had a great encounter.

604
00:31:40,658 --> 00:31:42,097
You know who gave me a ride?

605
00:31:42,858 --> 00:31:43,458
Who was it?

606
00:31:44,097 --> 00:31:44,737
Shen Mo.

607
00:31:44,737 --> 00:31:45,458
Liang Danning.

608
00:31:48,497 --> 00:31:49,138
Sir.

609
00:31:50,218 --> 00:31:51,017
Are you okay?

610
00:31:51,817 --> 00:31:53,418
Nothing serious. Just a few stitches.

611
00:31:53,737 --> 00:31:55,418
I just need seven days of rabies shots.

612
00:31:55,418 --> 00:31:57,577
You can't drink alcohol
during the rabies shots.

613
00:31:58,057 --> 00:31:58,577
Oh, no!

614
00:31:59,737 --> 00:32:02,297
But it's okay. I can still sell liquor
without drinking.

615
00:32:02,297 --> 00:32:03,097
Don't worry, boss.

616
00:32:03,178 --> 00:32:04,178
That's not what I meant.

617
00:32:04,898 --> 00:32:06,138
Just rest well for now.

618
00:32:07,618 --> 00:32:08,537
We'll take you home.

619
00:32:09,418 --> 00:32:10,337
No need.

620
00:32:10,858 --> 00:32:12,618
I appreciate the gesture, both of you.

621
00:32:12,618 --> 00:32:13,337
But,

622
00:32:13,337 --> 00:32:14,337
for now, I don't want

623
00:32:14,337 --> 00:32:15,658
my mom or my daughter to know

624
00:32:15,658 --> 00:32:16,817
about the dog bite.

625
00:32:17,577 --> 00:32:18,138
Another time.

626
00:32:18,658 --> 00:32:21,378
I'll treat you both to barbecue
at my place another day.

627
00:32:22,337 --> 00:32:24,138
Alright. Head home early then.

628
00:32:24,138 --> 00:32:24,737
Okay.

629
00:32:24,737 --> 00:32:26,537
Danning, this is for you.

630
00:32:27,378 --> 00:32:28,378
Thanks, boss.

631
00:32:28,497 --> 00:32:29,178
Got it?

632
00:32:29,178 --> 00:32:30,418
Yes.

633
00:32:30,678 --> 00:32:31,178
I'm off.

634
00:32:31,178 --> 00:32:32,337
Look at that.

635
00:32:34,138 --> 00:32:34,638
Honestly.

636
00:32:34,658 --> 00:32:36,458
Avoid spicy and irritating foods.

637
00:32:36,497 --> 00:32:37,378
Got it.

638
00:32:37,577 --> 00:32:38,337
Good night.

639
00:32:38,817 --> 00:32:40,017
Leaving now, boss. Bye.

640
00:32:40,898 --> 00:32:41,418
Bye.

641
00:32:45,378 --> 00:32:46,378
Danning has it tough.

642
00:32:47,737 --> 00:32:48,378
Yeah.

643
00:32:49,378 --> 00:32:52,138
But Liang Danning won't cause trouble
with the company over this.

644
00:32:52,458 --> 00:32:53,138
Don't worry.

645
00:32:53,658 --> 00:32:55,418
Even if she complains, I'd understand.

646
00:32:56,497 --> 00:32:57,218
But honestly,

647
00:32:57,817 --> 00:32:58,898
Danning may

648
00:32:59,138 --> 00:33:01,898
seem careless,
but she's actually very rational.

649
00:33:02,898 --> 00:33:04,817
Rational?
She's just got no other choice.

650
00:33:05,978 --> 00:33:07,138
Her burdens are heavy.

651
00:33:09,577 --> 00:33:10,378
I heard she is

652
00:33:11,658 --> 00:33:12,898
separated from her husband.

653
00:33:15,178 --> 00:33:17,138
He gambles and owes a lot of money.

654
00:33:20,458 --> 00:33:21,737
Anyway,

655
00:33:22,337 --> 00:33:23,698
even if she doesn't complain,

656
00:33:23,698 --> 00:33:25,938
what happened today was so unfair.

657
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:29,138
Who cares if they're clients?
They can't bully people like that!

658
00:33:29,698 --> 00:33:32,378
Too bad Liang Danning
isn't in the Promotions Department.

659
00:33:32,698 --> 00:33:34,938
Otherwise, I'd demand justice for her.

660
00:33:36,297 --> 00:33:37,138
I hear you.

661
00:33:38,898 --> 00:33:39,418
Do you?

662
00:33:39,858 --> 00:33:40,497
Here,

663
00:33:41,337 --> 00:33:44,297
how about I introduce Danning
to two new clients?

664
00:33:45,817 --> 00:33:46,317
Deal.

665
00:33:47,138 --> 00:33:48,577
I'll thank you for Danning.

666
00:33:48,577 --> 00:33:49,418
No problem.

667
00:33:50,337 --> 00:33:50,837
Let's go.

668
00:33:56,618 --> 00:33:57,418
Mom.

669
00:34:01,978 --> 00:34:03,138
Takeout today?

670
00:34:03,497 --> 00:34:04,297
Where's Grandma?

671
00:34:04,858 --> 00:34:05,817
She went to the shop.

672
00:34:06,938 --> 00:34:08,497
So you're home alone?

673
00:34:09,137 --> 00:34:11,378
Weiwei, dinner's ready.

674
00:34:13,657 --> 00:34:14,577
You're back so early.

675
00:34:16,097 --> 00:34:17,137
What are you doing here?

676
00:34:18,458 --> 00:34:20,938
Came to see Weiwei.
Haven't seen you in days.

677
00:34:25,137 --> 00:34:25,978
Let's eat.

678
00:34:25,978 --> 00:34:26,898
Keep your head back.

679
00:34:36,338 --> 00:34:37,617
Weiwei, come here.

680
00:34:37,738 --> 00:34:38,978
Let's stop watching for now.

681
00:34:39,978 --> 00:34:41,978
Dinner time soon.

682
00:34:42,057 --> 00:34:43,137
Come on, wash your hands.

683
00:34:43,697 --> 00:34:44,577
Okay.

684
00:34:45,338 --> 00:34:45,978
Here you go.

685
00:34:54,177 --> 00:34:54,697
What's wrong?

686
00:34:55,298 --> 00:34:55,798
Mom.

687
00:34:56,378 --> 00:34:57,418
How could you

688
00:34:57,418 --> 00:34:58,818
leave Weiwei to Yao Xiaohui?

689
00:34:59,137 --> 00:35:00,617
Good thing I came back.

690
00:35:01,537 --> 00:35:02,818
He didn't do anything to her.

691
00:35:02,858 --> 00:35:04,137
Besides, the shop was busy.

692
00:35:04,137 --> 00:35:05,978
I know that, but...

693
00:35:08,137 --> 00:35:09,057
Fine. Never mind.

694
00:35:09,418 --> 00:35:11,057
If you're busy,
don't bother coming back.

695
00:35:11,418 --> 00:35:12,418
I'm staying tonight.

696
00:35:13,497 --> 00:35:14,858
Okay, okay. I'll go now.

697
00:35:14,858 --> 00:35:15,778
Go ahead. Bye.

698
00:35:37,697 --> 00:35:38,298
Weiwei.

699
00:35:39,378 --> 00:35:40,378
You've lost weight again.

700
00:35:40,898 --> 00:35:41,398
Here.

701
00:35:42,738 --> 00:35:43,657
Eat more meat.

702
00:35:44,898 --> 00:35:45,938
Nourish yourself.

703
00:35:46,418 --> 00:35:48,697
Stay healthy to get good grades.

704
00:35:48,697 --> 00:35:50,298
Eat more vegetables too.

705
00:35:53,697 --> 00:35:54,197
Honey.

706
00:35:55,338 --> 00:35:56,097
I'll do it myself.

707
00:36:04,217 --> 00:36:05,617
Mom, what happened to your arm?

708
00:36:07,017 --> 00:36:07,818
It's nothing.

709
00:36:07,818 --> 00:36:08,778
Mom's fine.

710
00:36:08,778 --> 00:36:09,458
Let me see.

711
00:36:10,378 --> 00:36:12,057
Just a scratch, it's fine.

712
00:36:13,938 --> 00:36:15,097
Does it hurt?

713
00:36:15,458 --> 00:36:18,177
It doesn't hurt. Eat well, sweetie.

714
00:36:18,177 --> 00:36:19,177
Mom's not in pain.

715
00:36:19,778 --> 00:36:21,778
I told you this job isn't suitable.

716
00:36:21,898 --> 00:36:24,577
It's dangerous for a woman
to drink so much every day.

717
00:36:24,577 --> 00:36:26,378
What does danger
have to do with drinking?

718
00:36:27,338 --> 00:36:28,938
Some are dangerous without drinking.

719
00:36:29,418 --> 00:36:30,298
They go bankrupt.

720
00:36:39,458 --> 00:36:39,958
Weiwei.

721
00:36:40,938 --> 00:36:42,137
Have you had any exams lately?

722
00:36:42,898 --> 00:36:44,338
Just took one, all A's.

723
00:36:44,418 --> 00:36:45,217
Really?

724
00:36:46,697 --> 00:36:47,197
Awesome!

725
00:36:49,778 --> 00:36:50,537
See that?

726
00:36:50,537 --> 00:36:52,898
My daughter. That's my girl!

727
00:36:53,258 --> 00:36:54,938
Weiwei, actually,

728
00:36:54,938 --> 00:36:57,057
sometimes you shouldn't
always get perfect scores.

729
00:36:57,898 --> 00:36:59,097
It makes others dislike you.

730
00:36:59,697 --> 00:37:01,898
Getting a lower score
helps make friends, okay?

731
00:37:04,697 --> 00:37:05,458
Got it.

732
00:37:05,858 --> 00:37:07,537
How can you say that to our child?

733
00:37:23,577 --> 00:37:24,978
Mr. Danan, hello.

734
00:37:27,217 --> 00:37:28,497
I'm at home right now.

735
00:37:30,137 --> 00:37:31,057
Hold on a second.

736
00:37:32,017 --> 00:37:32,858
Um, I...

737
00:37:33,738 --> 00:37:34,617
Just a moment.

738
00:37:35,298 --> 00:37:36,458
Don't worry, Mr. Danan.

739
00:37:36,898 --> 00:37:37,537
No problem.

740
00:37:42,738 --> 00:37:45,057
I heard your teacher
mentioned in the group chat

741
00:37:45,057 --> 00:37:47,537
about an English speech performance.

742
00:37:47,537 --> 00:37:48,577
Did you participate?

743
00:37:48,898 --> 00:37:49,697
Oh, I know.

744
00:37:49,898 --> 00:37:50,898
I did.

745
00:37:51,298 --> 00:37:53,458
It's about how to make zongzi.

746
00:37:54,057 --> 00:37:54,978
It was really fun!

747
00:37:55,537 --> 00:37:57,217
Explain how to make zongzi in English?

748
00:37:57,298 --> 00:37:57,798
Yeah.

749
00:37:58,697 --> 00:38:00,217
Your school sure is interesting.

750
00:38:00,298 --> 00:38:00,898
Of course!

751
00:38:02,217 --> 00:38:04,738
Study hard. Mom suffered
because of poor language skills.

752
00:38:04,898 --> 00:38:05,938
I would've been promoted.

753
00:38:08,057 --> 00:38:09,017
Mom, eat more.

754
00:38:09,017 --> 00:38:09,978
Okay, you too.

755
00:38:12,537 --> 00:38:13,697
Going to play cards again?

756
00:38:14,697 --> 00:38:17,017
No, Mr. Danan needs to ask me something.

757
00:38:26,898 --> 00:38:29,818
Honey, since you're back,
I'll head out now.

758
00:38:29,978 --> 00:38:31,338
Okay, I'll take out the trash.

759
00:38:34,577 --> 00:38:36,378
Weiwei, Mom will be back soon.

760
00:38:37,217 --> 00:38:39,097
Weiwei, Dad's leaving now.

761
00:38:39,738 --> 00:38:40,778
Study hard at school.

762
00:38:41,338 --> 00:38:42,898
I'll come see you again later.

763
00:38:44,697 --> 00:38:46,057
Okay, bye.

764
00:38:46,577 --> 00:38:47,418
See you.

765
00:38:47,577 --> 00:38:48,458
Bye, Dad.

766
00:38:48,458 --> 00:38:49,298
Bye.

767
00:38:49,617 --> 00:38:50,418
Goodbye.

768
00:38:52,537 --> 00:38:54,898
See how nice it is
having dinner together?

769
00:38:55,298 --> 00:38:56,898
Let's give our child a complete family.

770
00:38:57,258 --> 00:38:58,978
Honey, let's not get divorced.

771
00:38:59,298 --> 00:39:00,017
Honey.

772
00:39:02,418 --> 00:39:02,918
You...

773
00:39:12,858 --> 00:39:14,017
Just let me explain.

774
00:39:14,017 --> 00:39:15,738
What's there to explain?

775
00:39:22,338 --> 00:39:23,097
Yao Xiaohui.

776
00:39:24,217 --> 00:39:26,497
I've tried saving your face
in front of our child.

777
00:39:27,418 --> 00:39:28,017
And you?

778
00:39:29,177 --> 00:39:30,778
You graduated from a nice university.

779
00:39:31,057 --> 00:39:32,057
But look at you now,

780
00:39:32,577 --> 00:39:33,978
lying and gambling.

781
00:39:34,778 --> 00:39:35,858
Now you're stealing too.

782
00:39:36,697 --> 00:39:38,617
And you ask why I want a divorce?

783
00:39:38,617 --> 00:39:39,938
Have you no shame?

784
00:39:42,458 --> 00:39:43,778
Honey, trust me one more time.

785
00:39:43,778 --> 00:39:44,497
Stop talking.

786
00:39:45,617 --> 00:39:46,137
Leave.

787
00:39:49,818 --> 00:39:50,537
Take this out.

788
00:39:58,217 --> 00:39:59,298
Mom's back!

789
00:40:20,243 --> 00:40:24,983
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

790
00:40:29,433 --> 00:40:31,353
♪Too much of shame♪

791
00:40:31,699 --> 00:40:34,495
♪To waste it crying♪

792
00:40:36,953 --> 00:40:38,873
♪Leave all behind you♪

793
00:40:38,873 --> 00:40:41,153
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

794
00:40:41,273 --> 00:40:43,502
♪You know how far you've gone♪

795
00:40:43,637 --> 00:40:45,913
♪In the fire you rise again♪

796
00:40:46,099 --> 00:40:48,459
♪You made it through the worst♪

797
00:40:48,597 --> 00:40:50,801
♪The best is yet to come♪

798
00:40:51,044 --> 00:40:53,184
♪The best is yet to come♪

799
00:40:55,886 --> 00:40:57,209
♪Isn't it magical♪

800
00:40:57,209 --> 00:40:58,841
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

801
00:40:58,873 --> 00:41:01,340
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

802
00:41:01,340 --> 00:41:03,793
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

803
00:41:03,874 --> 00:41:06,522
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

804
00:41:06,611 --> 00:41:09,142
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

805
00:41:09,222 --> 00:41:11,444
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

806
00:41:11,586 --> 00:41:12,667
♪But I don't want to♪

807
00:41:12,776 --> 00:41:15,042
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

808
00:41:15,158 --> 00:41:16,223
♪Until 3 AM♪

809
00:41:16,394 --> 00:41:17,599
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

810
00:41:17,753 --> 00:41:18,986
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

811
00:41:19,077 --> 00:41:21,441
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

812
00:41:21,588 --> 00:41:25,998
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

813
00:41:40,723 --> 00:41:42,159
♪Leave all behind you♪

814
00:41:42,263 --> 00:41:44,750
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

815
00:41:44,933 --> 00:41:47,062
♪You know how far you've gone♪

816
00:41:47,249 --> 00:41:49,589
♪In the fire you rise again♪

817
00:41:49,657 --> 00:41:51,923
♪You made it through the worst♪

818
00:41:52,283 --> 00:41:54,361
♪The best is yet to come♪

819
00:41:54,610 --> 00:41:56,780
♪The best is yet to come♪

820
00:41:59,481 --> 00:42:00,633
♪Isn't it magical♪

821
00:42:00,633 --> 00:42:04,279
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

822
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:06,169
♪And I see them sparkling♪

823
00:42:06,393 --> 00:42:08,524
♪Nobody knows♪

824
00:42:09,145 --> 00:42:11,055
♪What tomorrow brings♪

825
00:42:11,321 --> 00:42:13,644
♪You made it through the worst♪

826
00:42:13,831 --> 00:42:16,039
♪The best is yet to come♪

827
00:42:16,326 --> 00:42:18,475
♪The best is yet to come♪

828
00:42:18,771 --> 00:42:20,185
♪Isn't it magical♪

829
00:42:20,185 --> 00:42:22,397
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

830
00:42:22,471 --> 00:42:24,825
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

831
00:42:24,825 --> 00:42:25,913
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

832
00:42:25,913 --> 00:42:29,364
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

833
00:42:29,817 --> 00:42:32,091
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

834
00:42:32,505 --> 00:42:33,369
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

835
00:42:33,369 --> 00:42:34,889
♪Isn't it magical♪
